    <criteria>
      <textblock>
        Inclusion Criteria:

          -  Male/Female patients who are 55yrs or older and for whom carotid endarterectomy is
             clinically indicated and a decision has been made to perform a carotid endarterectomy.

          -  Normal liver and adequate renal function. Assessed by measuring eGFR (&gt;50ml/min) and
             creatinine (&lt;130μmol/L)

          -  Life expectancy &gt; 12 weeks

          -  Patients should be able to tolerate head/neck mask as well as lying in the PET-CT
             scanner

        Exclusion Criteria:

          -  Abnormal liver and renal function (eGFR &lt;50ml/min, Creatinine &gt;130μmol/L)

          -  Patient unwilling to provide written informed consent
      </textblock>
    </criteria>
